Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.qdl.extensions

Interface QDLModuleMetaClass

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Crypto, HTTPClient, QDLCLITools, QDLConvert, QDLDB, QDLMail
    public interface QDLModuleMetaClass
extends Serializable
    One way to make a Java module is to have a super class and have each method or variable defined as non-static inner classes. These then can share state between them. This interface should be implemented for those classes in order to ensure compatibility with the system. It has no methods and is a marker interface.
